First Time push : Follow the instructions given below the repo
To create a new branch and switch to it : git checkout -b "branchname"
To update the branch :

git add . ->to add all the changed files
git commit -m -> to  commit that change with a message
git checkout "branchname that you wanna switch to"-> to switch to a particular branch

git pull origin main -> To update all the changes that are made in main (Optional)

git merge "branchname"-> this branchname will be merged to the main

git push origin main -> to push the updated main to github

git push -u origin "branchname"-> to push this branch to github(not necessary to merge it to main)

Creating Individual Branches for Teammates — Clean Notes
1. Give Access to Teammates

From the main repo, add each teammate as a collaborator.
Go to: Repository → Settings → Collaborators & Teams
Ensure all teammates have proper access (Write access).


2. Teammates Clone the Repo
Each teammate clones the repository locally:
git clone <repo-url>


3. View All Remote Branches
Before creating or switching to a branch, teammates can view all remote branches using:
git branch -r

This shows something like:
origin/main
origin/user1-branch
origin/user2-branch


4. Create & Track Their Own Branch
If a matching remote branch already exists (created by admin), teammates can link to it locally:
git checkout -b <branch-name> origin/<branch-name>

Meaning:

-b <branch-name> → creates a local branch
origin/<branch-name> → connects it to the remote branch

Example:
git checkout -b john-feature origin/john-feature


5. Or Create a Fresh Branch (if not created already)
If they want to create a brand‑new branch:
git checkout -b <new-branch>
git push -u origin <new-branch>




